{
  "stem": "15962.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- after a few days of having to stay in the same barracks, we were allowed to move around a little more during certain hours of the day, and to reunite family and meet my mother, and exchange experiences and find either relatives of friends that preceded us to this camp.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Birkenau was an enormous camp made out of literally hundreds of huge barracks that were originally designed as stables for horses.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was-- they were made out of wood, the roof was held by roof trusses with a band of narrow windows at the top.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] bunk beds lining the sides with a horizontal chimney that had two vertical chimneys at each end that was sometimes used for minimal heating in the bitter winter.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, there were maybe 150 feet long, and there were several hundred people in each barrack.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were-- the bunk beds were three layers high, and there were six people on each horizontal bunk bed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were literally, when the camp was full, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sandwiched in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one person couldn't arbitrarily turn over.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would have to-- the whole row would have to turn over.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was very, very compressed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And to go to relieve yourself at night was extremely excruciating.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We couldn't leave the barrack.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were buckets that quickly overflowed at the doorways.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And every night, they were stacked up near the door, and usually the clothing was stripped by others because there was a-- especially in the winter, there was such a shortage of clothing that a pair of socks or gloves was very highly valued.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The-- at the end of-- each camp was surrounded-- each compartment was surrounded by-- by wire, barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
